# Mintlify Docs Site Rules

When editing files in `docs-site/`:

## docs.json navigation

- Navigation page entries MUST be plain strings, not objects.
  - Correct: `"pages": ["quickstart", "cli", "mcp"]`
  - Wrong: `"pages": [{ "page": "quickstart", "icon": "rocket" }]`
- Page icons go in each `.mdx` file's YAML frontmatter (`icon: "rocket"`), not in `docs.json`.
- The `navigation` object uses `groups` with `group` + `pages` arrays. Do not invent keys like `products`, `versions`, `tabs`, or `languages` unless explicitly needed.

## Special files

- The AI assistant file MUST be named `Assistant.md` (capital A). Mintlify will not detect `assistant.md`.
- The config file MUST be `docs.json` (not `mint.json`).

## Reserved routes

- `/mcp` is reserved by Mintlify's built-in MCP server. Do NOT name a docs page `mcp.mdx` — it will be hijacked by the MCP endpoint. Use `mcp-connector.mdx` instead.
- Check Mintlify docs for other reserved routes before creating new page filenames.

## Content scope

- This docs site is for the public OSS agent kit only.
- Do not document internal cloud repo code, web repo code, or multi-repo architecture.
- The hosted cloud page should only explain what the hosted product adds on top of the OSS kit.
- All copy must follow the OpenPasture voice: plain, practical, farmer-to-farmer, uncertainty-aware, no overclaimed autonomy.

## Validation

Always run before committing docs-site changes:

```bash
cd docs-site
python3 -m json.tool docs.json > /dev/null  # JSON syntax
npx mint@latest broken-links                  # link check
```

## Available Mintlify features

- Themes: `mint`, `maple`, `palm`, `willow`, `linden`, `almond`, `aspen`, `sequoia`, `luma`
- Page frontmatter: `title`, `description`, `icon`, `sidebarTitle`, `tag`, `mode` (`wide`, `custom`, `frame`, `center`)
- MDX components: `Card`, `CardGroup`, `Steps`, `Step`, `Info`, `Warning`, `Tip`, `Note`, `Tabs`, `Tab`, `Accordion`, `AccordionGroup`
- Background decorations: `gradient`, `grid`, `windows`
- Icon libraries: `lucide` (current), `fontawesome`, `tabler`
- Code block themes: any Shiki theme name, or `{ "light": "...", "dark": "..." }`
